I play on Old UI on one computer and New UI on another- the below information applies to both UI's<br>
I disable all new models (although i believe all you need to disable is your own sex / race and horses / elementals)<br>
I have ALL the advantages and none of the disadvantages:<br>
-no horse head in view ever<br>
-no slow start / stop<br>
-no problem with SoW / Jboots sticking and working properly<br>
-no problem with ducking to interrupt<br>
-no problem with aggro when sitting<br>
-mana regen does occur as if you were medding when you stand still or spin in place only, ALTHOUGH you wont actually see the mana regen UNTIL YOU CAST OR ROD at which point your mana will shoot upward the appropriate amount.<br>
-no problem targetting mobs to loot or attack (although a very unusual thing does occur that i call the &quot;invisible lump&quot; at the exact spot i am standing when i summon the horse.  Other players experience this spot too.  Basically there is an invisible &quot;object&quot; that you can not run through and that if you try to target THROUGH it you will end up targeting yourself just like if you hit F1....not an issue if you summon your horse away from your camp spot a bit.)<br>
<br>
Only problems:<br>
-no Kewl new models to look at<br>
-occasional difficutly of healers targeting you due to &quot;out of range&quot; message (this occurs whether or not you have horse models on)  for which circumstances i just click off the horse buff icon if i am needing a heal.<br>
-occasional difficulty trading with other players, again because of what i presume to be the server interpreting that you are too far away.  Again i just click off horse icon and trade then resummon.<br>
-Lastly I am not sure, but I dont think you get the horses &quot;speed buff&quot; for high end horses.  But i have the pokey one only for mana regen / aggro puroposes so this doesnt affect me, and i would rather have SoW / boots up anyhow.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps<br>
IMHO An excellent investment for 7.5 kpp used in this fashion.<br>
<br>
