One of the nice things about it is how fast you can get back to dealing damage after a death/rez.  I re-equip, take a rod shot, summon a pet/horse and start staff nuking.  Yeah I'm OOM, but I'm doing nuke damage while medding <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cicelygoldenfair>cicely goldenfair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 5:35:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7868.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: omg</span><hr size=1> for the longest time, i told myself i would never purchase a horse because i could not see myself spending 8k on a travel item.  when the new expansion came out, and all the outdoor zones were introduced, a lot of people started talking about the advantages of having a horse with regards to mana regeneration.  after a few xp ventures in plane of valor, when i found myself needing to wait before i could cast more spells... i gave in.  i purchased the cheapest horse you can get (tan/brown is the lowest, followed by black/white).  my sole purpose and use of the horse was/is when i am not pulling in an xp group, and it would be used simply to regain mana.<br>
<br>
after a few more xp journeys, i am proud to say that this is probably one of the best purchases i have ever made in my 3 year gaming career.  using boots of bladecalling, and being able to regain approx 60 mana or so during the cast of the boots is invaluable.  it allows me to regain mana much faster, which in turn allows me to cast more spells and inflict more damage.<br>
<br>
for pure mana regeneration purposes, horses = win<br>
<br>
if you desire a horse for fast travel, save your money and purchase the 100k horse.  that is the only horse that will be worth the money, as far as speed...<br>
