<br>
One of the things people forget about when they figure the cost of nukes is the opportunity cost (for lack of a better term).  I.E.  the duration of the cast is time you're not medding.  As you point out, that's an extra 60mana during the cast of BoBC.  The horse removes this almost entirely.  When I'm on my horse there is no reason not to be always mid cast.  Staff nuke early, real nukes later, or to finish.  Considering that the damage bracer affects BWS - I can put out somewhere around 28dps while OOM (and have had too after a rez - I use my presummoned rod for enough mana for a pet and BOIV)<br>
<br>
Only thing I don't like about the staff is the LOS restriction.<br>
Unfortunately, the attrition in my guild has taken us away from being able to do Velk, instead of nearer.<br>
